# Blog Post Authoring

## Article queue: `.ignore/webpages.json`

`.ignore/webpages.json` is the master list of articles to be converted into blog posts. Each entry has:

```json
{
  "id": 28193,
  "date": "2025-07-25T19:27:31",
  "link": "https://nuvigant.com/blog/industry/aml/que-son-los-peps-para-notarios",
  "title": { "rendered": "Qué son los PEPS para notarios" },
  "finished": true
}
```

- **`finished: true`** — the post has already been created. **Skip it.**
- **`finished` absent or `false`** — the post still needs to be created.

**After successfully creating a post**, update the corresponding entry in `.ignore/webpages.json` by setting `"finished": true`. Use the `StrReplace` tool to make the change — find the entry by its `"id"` or `"link"` and add/set the field.

When asked to convert or batch-process articles, always read `.ignore/webpages.json` first to determine which entries are pending (no `finished` field or `finished: false`), process only those, and mark each one finished as soon as its post file is created.

## Creating a post from an external URL

Always use `WebFetch` on the source URL — never rely on a text-only scrape.
The text scraper strips `href` values; WebFetch returns full markdown with working links.

```
✅ WebFetch("https://nuvigant.com/blog/industry/lawyers/some-post")
❌ Using the external_links context alone — hrefs will be missing
```

After fetching, **always** extract the original publication date from the page source and use it as the `date` field in frontmatter — never default to today's date or invent one:

```bash
curl -s "<url>" | grep -oP '(?<=<time[^>]*datetime=")[^"]+' | head -3
# fallback: look for visible date text patterns like DD/MM/YY or Month DD, YYYY
curl -s "<url>" | grep -oP '\d{2}/\d{2}/\d{2,4}' | head -3
```

Convert the result to `YYYY-MM-DD` format for the frontmatter `date` field.

After fetching, **always** check for an embedded YouTube video — WebFetch strips iframes so the video will not appear in the output. Extract it from the raw page source:

```bash
curl -s "<url>" | grep -o 'youtube\.com/embed/[^"?]*' | head -5
```

If a video ID is found, embed it in the markdown right after the intro paragraph using a responsive wrapper:

```html
<div class="video-container"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID" title="..." allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
```

The `.video-container` class is defined in `src/app/globals.css` and provides a 16:9 responsive embed with rounded corners. Do **not** add inline styles.

## Frontmatter requirements

Every post **must** include `category` and `subcategory`. The filename must match the intended URL slug exactly.

```yaml
---
title: "..."
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
author:
  name: "Equipo Nuvigant"
  avatar: "https://ui-avatars.com/api/?name=Equipo+Nuvigant&background=056dfe&color=fff&size=128"
  bio: "..."
  twitter: "https://twitter.com/nuvigant"
  linkedin: "https://linkedin.com/company/nuvigant"
tags: ["Tag1", "Tag2"]
excerpt: "..."
coverImage: "/images/blog/post-slug.jpg"  # local path, never an external URL
published: true
category: "industry"       # ← required
subcategory: "lawyers"     # ← required
---
```

- **Filename = slug**: `content/posts/puede-la-ia-sustituir-al-notario.md` → `/blog/industry/lawyers/puede-la-ia-sustituir-al-notario`
- **Unique cover images**: never reuse the same image across posts
- **Images are local**: download covers to `public/images/blog/<post-slug>.jpg` with `curl -sL "<unsplash-url>&fm=jpg" -o <post-slug>.jpg`; reference as `/images/blog/<post-slug>.jpg` — never use external Unsplash URLs directly
- **Preserve all links**: include every `href` from the original, including inline article links and the "clic aquí" style CTAs
- **Always include a body image**: every post must have at least one inline image relevant to the topic. Download it to `public/images/blog/<post-slug>-body.jpg` and embed it as `![post-title-with-dashes-instead-of-spaces](/images/blog/<post-slug>-body.jpg)`. The alt text must be the post title with spaces replaced by `-` (e.g. `Exención-casa-habitación-mixta-¿cómo-funciona?`).
- **Never place two images, or a YouTube video and an image, next to each other**: always separate them with at least one full section of body text (a heading + paragraph) between them.

## Body text alignment

All paragraph text in blog posts is **justified**. This is enforced by setting `text-align: justify` on `.blog-content` in `src/app/globals.css`, which inherits to all children. Headings (`h2`, `h3`, `h4`) explicitly override back to `text-align: left`.
Do not override this with inline styles or Tailwind classes on individual posts.

## When adding a new post, also add a redirect in `next.config.ts`

```ts
{ source: "/blog/old-slug", destination: "/blog/category/subcategory/old-slug", permanent: true }
```

## After creating a new post, open it in the browser

Once the markdown file is saved, derive the full URL path from the frontmatter:

```
/blog/<category>/<subcategory>/<slug>
```

where `<slug>` is the filename without the `.md` extension. Then open that path in both environments using the Shell tool:

```bash
xdg-open "http://localhost:3000/blog/<category>/<subcategory>/<slug>"
xdg-open "https://nuvigant.com/blog/<category>/<subcategory>/<slug>"
```

Both tabs must be opened every time a new post is created, without waiting to be asked.
